<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. The call memchr(name_ptr, 0, OS_MAX_FILE_NAME) can read a fixed number of bytes starting at name_ptr without guaranteeing that that many bytes are valid within the VirtualPath object. name_ptr is derived from strrchr(VirtualPath,'/') and may point near the end of the VirtualPath string. If the remaining bytes from name_ptr to the end of the VirtualPath buffer are less than OS_MAX_FILE_NAME (for example VirtualPath = "/a" and OS_MAX_FILE_NAME is large), memchr will access bytes beyond the bounds of the VirtualPath object, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
